Now, we determine if the group G is isomorphic to C8, Q8, or D4. Since G has order 8, it can be isomorphic to any of these three groups. To determine which one, we need to look at the properties of the group G.

- If G is cyclic, it is isomorphic to C8.
- If G has a unique subgroup of order 4 and every element has order 2 or 4, it is isomorphic to Q8.
- If G has more than one subgroup of order 4 and has elements of order 2, it is isomorphic to D4.

